</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t give investing advice =
around here, but the other day I did <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/25866447.270656/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlu=
aW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMjIvYmUtY2FyZWZ1bC13aXRoLXZvbGNhbm8tYm9uZHM_Y21=
waWQ9QkJEMTEyOTIxX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3=
NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjExMTI5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cBeb4e272d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targe=
t=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: s=
olid; background-color: #ccc;"> have some nice things to say</a> about the =
El Salvador 8.25% bond due in 2032. Relatively nice things, anyway. Last we=
ek El Salvador announced that it was issuing a $1 billion =E2=80=9Cvolcano =
bond,=E2=80=9D a 6.5% bond due in 2032 that will be issued on a blockchain,=
 will be pitched to crypto fans, and will come with a call option on $250 m=
illion of Bitcoin. I said, well, instead of buying that, you can buy the 8.=
25% bond for about 75 cents on the dollar and put the other 25 cents into b=
uying Bitcoin. That way you get a higher yield (8.25% is more than 6.5%) an=
d more Bitcoin exposure ($25 worth of Bitcoin is a bit more Bitcoin than an=
 at-the-money call option on $25 of Bitcoin).=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">How is that working out? I really must emphasize that nothing here=
 is ever investing advice; here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/25866447.270656/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMjYvZWwtc2FsdmFkb3ItYm91Z2h0LXRoZS1kaXAtYWNxdW=
lyaW5nLTEwMC1tb3JlLWJpdGNvaW4_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEyOTIxX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZ=
Gl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjExMTI5JnV0bV9jYW1w=
YWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB56e13e84" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> a Bloomber=
g article from Friday</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Doll=
ar bonds from El Salvador are among the worst-performing in emerging market=
s so far this month, lagging only defaulted Lebanese debt, according to dat=
a compiled from a Bloomberg index.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Th=
e selloff in the bonds came as investors weighed the possibility of higher =
indebtedness in the Central American nation, as well as rising concern it w=
ill not reach a deal with the International Monetary Fund.=C2=A0</p></block=
quote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CBitcoin Bond Plan Sends El Salv=
ador=E2=80=99s Dollar Debt Diving,=E2=80=9D says <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25866447.270656/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTEtMjIvYml0Y29pbi1ib25kLW9uLWhvcml6b24tc2V=
uZHMtZWwtc2FsdmFkb3Itcy1kb2xsYXItZGVidC1kaXZpbmc_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTEyOTIxX01PTk=
VZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09M=
jExMTI5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9b688191" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;"> this Bloomberg headline</a> from early last week. And those 8.25% =
bonds now seem to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
25866447.270656/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm91cnNlLmx1L3NlY3VyaXR5L1hTMDE0NjE3MzM3MS8=
1NjY1Mw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcc3da5b7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">trade at about 68 cents =
on the dollar</a>, down about 10% from when we last discussed them. Oh well=
.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In some vague financial theory, if El Sal=
vador succeeds in issuing these volcano bonds, somebody should (1) buy the =
8.25% bonds and some Bitcoin along the lines I proposed, (2) short the volc=
ano bonds and (3) collect a risk-free profit. Arguably this should be=C2=A0=
<em>good=C2=A0</em>for the price of El Salvador=E2=80=99s existing debt.</p=
><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But in practice it seems very hard to actuall=
y do the arbitrage here.=C2=A0The only people realistically buying El Salva=
dor=E2=80=99s 8.25% bonds are, like, grizzled emerging-markets veterans. Th=
ose bonds do not trade in particularly convenient ways; the average retail =
speculator is not going to go buy them. Those grizzled veterans might or mi=
ght not be able to buy Bitcoin to complete the long side of the arbitrage; =
if you run an emerging-market fund it is not obvious that your mandate woul=
d allow buying Bitcoin. Meanwhile I do not know a lot about the blockchain =
apparatus that will be used to issue the volcano bonds, but I am going to g=
uess that (1) neither do those emerging-markets veterans and (2) it probabl=
y will not make it=C2=A0<em>easy=C2=A0</em>to short the volcano bonds.=C2=
=A0So doing the arbitrage involves trading three markets =E2=80=94=C2=A0EM =
bonds, Bitcoin, and short selling on the volcano bond=E2=80=99s blockchain =
platform =E2=80=94=C2=A0that do not have a lot of overlap.=C2=A0</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile the people buying El Salvador=E2=80=99s 6.5=
% Bitcoin bonds will be, like, crypto fans who enjoy going to crypto partie=
s with El Salvador=E2=80=99s crypto-bro president.=C2=A0<em>They=C2=A0</em>=
are not going to go figure out how to buy the 8.25% bond to get better econ=
omics than the volcano bond; that requires using antiquated traditional-fin=
ance infrastructure and won=E2=80=99t get them invited to the parties. I su=
spect that El Salvador=E2=80=99s efforts at market segmentation will just w=
ork; there is no reason for the price of its volcano bonds to track the pri=
ce of its regular bonds, and they probably won=E2=80=99t.=C2=A0</p><table c=
lass=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellpadding=
=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Everything is securities fraud</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is it securities fraud to refuse to se=
ll ice cream in the occupied Palestinian territories? Folks, <a href=3D"htt=
ps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25866447.270656/aHR0cHM6Ly9ueXBv=
c3QuY29tLzIwMjEvMTEvMjcvdG9ycmVzLWFza3Mtc2VjLXRvLXJldmlldy1maWxpbmdzLW92ZXI=
tYmVuLWplcnJ5cy1pc3JhZWwtYm95Y290dC8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2c412329" ite=
mprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"colo=
r: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #c=
cc;">everything is securities fraud</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">A Bronx congressman is asking the Securities and Exchange Commiss=
ion to demand the parent company of Ben &amp; Jerrys to amend their regulat=
ory filings to reflect potential new risks caused by the woke ice cream mak=
er=E2=80=99s decision to no longer peddle its products in parts of Israel.<=
/p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Participating in the Boycott Divestment and=
 Sanctions movement against Israel can result in potentially stiff financia=
l consequences in more than 30 states =E2=80=94 including New York, which h=
as moved to divest more than $100 million in pension funds from Unilever.</=
p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CUnilever is a widely held company w=
